The paper focuses on human-robot interaction and learning from user preferences to improve robot behavior. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of active preference learning and machine learning techniques also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the application of these techniques to industrial facilities and material transport tasks suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
